    "summary": "<strong>Communications is the heaviest instructional area in this set, worth roughly <strong>9 questions per 100-question BMA ICDC exam</strong></strong> — so master it and you bank nearly a tenth of your score. It spans written business documents (letters, memos, reports, persuasive messages), oral skills (presentations, phone calls, meetings, facilitation), and the meta-skills of <strong>listening, paraphrasing, and choosing the right channel</strong>. DECA almost always tests this with realistic workplace scenarios, so think \"what would a professional actually do\" rather than memorizing definitions.",
