    "traps": "Don't confuse a <strong>brand promise</strong> (what the business commits to <em>provide</em>, connecting emotionally) with a slogan or logo. Remember customers form <strong>one overall impression</strong> regardless of how many <strong>touch points</strong> they hit — so consistency matters everywhere. For difficult customers, the answer is always <strong>courtesy and patience</strong>, never confronting them about their attitude. And the top complaint driver is <strong>poor product quality</strong> — be wary of distractor options like price cuts or longer hours, which actually <em>please</em> customers."
